2-Function Scope :-Var Hamara Function Scope HOta hai Sirf us function ke andar accessible hoga agar Function ke bahar ❌ error
Example 
function test() {
  var a = 10;
}

console.log(a); // ❌ Error


Agar var {} ke andar bana
Wo pura function me accessible hoga
Example :-

function test() {
  if (true) {
    var x = 20;
  }

  console.log(x); // ✅ chalega
}
Function ko maanta hai

Block ko ignore karta hai 
Tumne var x ko block me likha

BUT JavaScript ne usko aise treat kiya jaise yeh function ke top pe likha ho.//// Important
function test() {
  var x =10;      // hoisted to function top

  if (true) {
    x = 10;
  }

  console.log(x);
}




2- Block Scope :- let aur const Block Scoped hote hain { } ke bahar access nahi hoga
function test() {
  if (true) {
    let x = 10;
    const y = 20;
  }

  console.log(x); // ❌ Error
  console.log(y); // ❌ Error
}

x aur y sirf if block ke andar exist karte hain
Block ke bahar unka wajood hi nahi



Function ke andar (no inner block):-
