JavaScript ka kaam karne ka tareeka:-
1-Memory Creation Phase
Variables ko memory me jagah milti hai
Functions pura store ho jate hain
2- Execution Phase
Code line by line execute hota hai



Ab dekho var ke saath kya hota hai

Example:-
console.log(a);
var a = 10;


Memory Phase me:
a = undefined


Execution Phase:
console.log(a); → undefined
a = 10;
Isliye error nahi aata.



Ab let ke saath dekho:-
console.log(b);
let b = 20;
Memory Phase me:
b = <uninitialized>
⚠️ Yaha difference hai.
var ko undefined milta hai
let ko milta hai: uninitialized

Execution Phase:

Jab tak let b = 20 wali line nahi aati
Tab tak b TDZ me rehta hai

Isliye error aata hai.
